                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/471.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have received telegraphic
                    instructions from my Government to call to your excellency’s attention the
                    situation prevailing in the capital of Mexico where, in spite of the guaranties
                    offered by the Chief of the Zapatista forces, several Spaniards have been
                    murdered and houses owned by our people have been plundered and sequestered
                    while our diplomatic representative does not even know of any one to apply to
                    for due redress and discontinuance of such acts.</p>
                <p>In thus carrying out my instructions, I avail [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
